      <p>Delta bluesmen were often solo performers, which meant they had to act as their own band. This led to incredible rhythmic innovations. Robert Johnson, perhaps the most famous of all Delta blues figures, perfected a style where his thumb would maintain a steady 'walking' bass line on the lower strings while his fingers played intricate melodies and chord stabs on the higher strings. This level of independence is one of the greatest challenges for any guitarist. Our 'Independence Modules' break this down into manageable steps, showing you how to separate your brain from your thumb. Mastering this 'one-man-band' approach is the key to creating a sound that is both musically complex and rhythmically driving, a hallmark of the Delta style.</p>

